"Indigenous peoples" is a collective name for the original peoples of North America and their descendants. The Canadian Constitution recognizes 3 groups of Indigenous peoples: First Nations, Inuit, Métis. These are 3 distinct peoples with unique histories, languages, cultural practices and spiritual beliefs. Please review the definition of Indigenous/Aboriginal people in the previous statement. The Coming Soon value in the Tenants prompt enables you to filter for early What's New documentation that we publish 1 week before the Preview feature release. Items are only marked Coming Soon in the week prior to the Preview feature release, after which we update them to show the tenant we deliver them to.

Important: Use the System Subcategories prompt to narrow results for features in the System functional area. You must have System enabled in your tenant or selected in the prompt to have a System Subcategory impact your search results."
